deck: Oscar Stamp was a young man living in 19th century London whom became the adoptive father to the young boy Daniel Summers. In this, playing a vital role as an sort-of ancestor to the Summers family.
description:
Origin

Oscar Stamp was a poor young man whom lived in 19th century London. Not much is known about his past other then that he fled from his parents due to abuse.

Creation

Oscar Stamp was created by Peter Milligan and John Paul Leon and first appeared in The Further Adventures of Cyclops and Phoenix issue 1 (1996). He changed his name to Oscar Summers at the end of issue 4 of the same series.

Major Story Arcs

A Marauder

Oscar joined a band of man whom named themselves the Marauders whom tasked themselves with capturing unusual and disfigured people in the London area. Although Oscar himself was a slaver of these people, the captives found Oscar to be one of the more gentle figures. Eventually Oscar came into contact with the time-displaced X-men Cyclops and Phoenix, whom helped save him when the former slaves of Essex where freed. In return, Oscar helped out the pair of mutants and even formed a friendship with one former slave, a young boy named Daniel. Together with Daniel, Oscar would travel to America with Oscar posing as his father. They took on the name "Summers" as their last name when entering America, after their rescuers Scott and Jean Summers. Oscar has not been seen since and is presumed dead.
name: Oscar Stamp

deck: Vulture von Doom is a pet of Doctor Doom.
description:
Origin

Vulture von Doom is a vulture with the same characteristics as his owner, Doctor Doom: vain and hellbent on world domination. He once abducted several members of the Pet Avengers to tap them of their residual energy they still had from their encounter with the Infinity Gauntlet. The remaining members of the Pet Avengers broke Vulture's machine, thus thwarting his plans.

deck: Khalid "Kent" Nassour is a Brooklyn Medical student and the newest bearer of the Helm of Fate. Born to an American mother and an Egyptian father, Khalid is the descendant of pharaohs from ages past. Now Khalid struggles to balance his college education, his social life, and the burden of Fate, all while learning how to use his newfound powers, and using them to battle the Gods that would seek to undo the world.
description: Note: In the DC Sneak Peek that marked his debut, Khalid and his father's last name was given as Nassour. However, in the first issue of his new series, their last name was changed to Nelson. The 2nd issue changed their last name back to Nassour.
